{
  "stem": "894.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so we clung together, and they lined us up.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And as we walked forward, I remember looking back, and I saw-- you know, being that it was a very Hasidic town, and a lot of very religious Jews, mostly wore beards and black hats.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And so, when I looked back to see my father, I could never make out who-- anymore where he is or-- I never saw him again once we got off the train.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Never had a chance to say a word to him or him to me.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Because when the doors slid open, they started screeching.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And you know, you felt panicky and scared.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And then we walked towards this famous Dr.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Mengele, who was sitting at a table with some others.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "As I recall, he wasn't alone.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] my two sisters were on the right side of my mother.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I was on the left side of my mother, holding her arm as usual.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I could see, you know, that each person or family that approached that table-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] that there is a separation.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But I don't know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I always say it was an angel who take care of me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Because I really wasn't going to let go of my mother.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Because wherever she went, I wanted to go.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But there were just one more row of people in front of us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "It would've been our turn next.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I pulled my hand out from my mother.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I ran in between my two sisters, and I took them.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And literally a second later, Mengele said, the three of you go right and for my mother to go left.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it just took that instant.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
